<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="487" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,545,1002]" pageId="18" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,869,894]" pageId="18" pageNumber="487">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males distinguished from all other genera in Pyriglenini by plain gray plumage with darker wing coverts and white wing covert spots combined with absence of white interscapular patch. Female plumage similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[183,284,941,966]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Sclateria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="487" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[183,284,941,966]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="487">Sclateria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but distinguished by gray on head or upperparts (except 
<taxonomicName box="[957,1080,941,966]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmelastes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="487" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="humaythae">
<emphasis box="[957,1080,941,966]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="487">humaythae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and lack of pale superciliary. Differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[298,399,977,1002]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Sclateria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="487" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[298,399,977,1002]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="487">Sclateria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in bill proportions (bill width and depth compared to length) and tail movements.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
